official tutorial  
http://rogerdudler.github.io/git-guide/
Workflow:
Working Directory-(add)->Index-(commit)->Head

Initialization
create a new directory and copy its address #D#
git init
git remote add origin #D# (To tell the git where your barn is)
git config  --global user.name "your name"
git config  --global user.email "your email address"

Checkout a repository
git clone /path/to/repository (to create a working copy of a local repository)
OR
git clone username@host:/path/to/repository (when using a remote server)

Add & Commit
git add <filename>
git commit -m "A description of this commit" (The file is committed to the HEAD, but not in your remote repository yet.)

Pushing Changes
git push origin #DB# (To send those changes to your remote repository and branch DB)
Now your changes have been pushed to the website and go to github.com:
repository->branches->merge request
(before a check, all the commits on this branch will require an update)

Branching
git checkout branch_a (switch back to branch_a)
git checkout -b branch_x (create a new branch named "branch_x" and switch to it )
git branch -d branch_x (delete the branch_x)
git push origin <branch> (push the branch to your remote repository)

Update & Merge
git pull (update your local repository to the newest commit)
git diff <source_branch> <target_branch> (have a check before mergin)
git add <filename> (to handle the conflicts)

Replace local changes
git checkout -- <filename> (Replace local changes with the last content in HEAD)
OR Replace local changes with the last content in the server
git fetch origin
git reset --hard origin/master
tagging
git tag name #the first 10 characters of the commit id#


